cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the impact of different text representations on NLP tasks, specifically in a morphologically rich language.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the training of word embeddings using different methods and compares their performance on various tasks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of word embeddings in NLP tasks, which is a common application of AI.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural network-based models for training word embeddings.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of different text representations on language model tasks, which involve the use of algorithms and data structures.
